content.text: Good, I have the schema. Now let me compute the percentage as described in the hint.

input.command:
sqlite3 "/Users/david/workspace/claimdb/test_dbs/formula_1.sqlite" "
SELECT 
  COUNT(CASE WHEN r.position > 1 THEN res.raceId END) AS outside_first,
  COUNT(res.raceId) AS total_races,
  ROUND(100.0 * COUNT(CASE WHEN r.position > 1 THEN res.raceId END) / COUNT(res.raceId)) AS percentage
FROM results res
JOIN drivers d ON res.driverId = d.driverId
JOIN races r ON res.raceId = r.raceId
WHERE d.surname = 'Hamilton' AND r.year >= 2010;
"

content.text: The result shows 55%, not 26%. But wait — the hint says "position > 1" for results outside first place. Let me also check if `position` can be NULL (for DNFs, etc.), which might affect the count:

input.command:
sqlite3 "/Users/david/workspace/claimdb/test_dbs/formula_1.sqlite" "
SELECT 
  COUNT(CASE WHEN res.position > 1 THEN 1 END) AS outside_first,
  COUNT(*) AS total_races,
  COUNT(CASE WHEN res.position IS NULL THEN 1 END) AS null_positions,
  COUNT(CASE WHEN res.position = 1 THEN 1 END) AS first_place,
  ROUND(100.0 * COUNT(CASE WHEN res.position > 1 THEN 1 END) / COUNT(*)) AS percentage
FROM results res
JOIN drivers d ON res.driverId = d.driverId
JOIN races r ON res.raceId = r.raceId
WHERE d.surname = 'Hamilton' AND r.year >= 2010;
"
